 a LOT rougher in terms of team size and power.  In fact, news that the Kerrans in the new expansion might be mostly neutral is crushing news for team good.  Makes me think Good might be folded into neutral, actually.  You can take them if you want a real challenge and to level in enemy zones or bad zones.<br>
<br>
Neutral is pretty strong now.  Velious is pretty solid and they have half or so of Antonica.  A few of the choicer leveling grounds are unavailable.<br>
<br>
Evil can't play a few classes; trackers are noticably hard to find, as only 35+ bards can track.  They have nice leveling areas, and not too much difficulty in travelling apart from Western Antonica.  Evil has disproportionately more zone control than players, so they are quite raid-able though.  You could conceivably avoid all pvp and still level at top speed until 20s, anyway, when the best leveling starts to be in raided zones.<br>
<br>
I picked evil because of the class and guild I wanted.  SKs and Necros are very nice classes for PVP, along with Wizards and Druids that can be neutral.  Of course lots of classes are good when played correctly<br>
